      Euphemisms
   =20
 =20

I don=E2=80=99t know, if you are running an international money laundering =
group, and you=E2=80=99re doing it over a group chat:=C2=A0
=09Probably just don=E2=80=99t do that? Talk in person? It=E2=80=99s hard, =
though, I get it; Whatsapp is more convenient.=09
Definitely=C2=A0don=E2=80=99t name your group chat, like, =E2=80=9CInternat=
ional Money Laundering Group Chat,=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9CCrime LOL,=E2=80=9D=
 or =E2=80=9Cthe Cartel,=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9CProsecutors Don=E2=80=99t Loo=
k at This One!=E2=80=9D=09I=C2=A0guess=C2=A0you could name it, like, =E2=80=
=9CImport/Export Travel Chat,=E2=80=9D something neutral and professional.=
=09At the margin, naming it =E2=80=9CSunshine and Lollipops=E2=80=9D is pro=
bably bad?

Anyway:

A network of couriers who jointly smuggled more than =C2=A3100 million ($12=
4 million) of criminal cash in suitcases from the UK to Dubai was found gui=
lty following a trial of one of the largest money laundering scams ever rec=
orded.
In total 11 couriers have been convicted alongside the ringleader, the Nati=
onal Crime Agency said Wednesday. In less than a year, the couriers flew mo=
re than 80 flights, carrying cases full of drug money. The group communicat=
ed on a Whatsapp group called=C2=A0Sunshine and Lollipops.

I frequently  point out that giving bribes cutesy names in written communic=
ations is bad, because when you go to trial and a prosecutor says =E2=80=9C=
and in this email you promised a government official =E2=80=981 million lol=
lipops,=E2=80=99 and those weren=E2=80=99t lollipops now were they,=E2=80=
=9D you will not have a good answer and will look very guilty. Naming your =
money-laundering group chat =E2=80=9CSunshine and Lollipops=E2=80=9D seems =
a little less obviously bad; you have to name the chat something and everyo=
ne=E2=80=99s chats have dumb jokey names. Still the jury is not going to li=
ke you=C2=A0more=C2=A0for that name.
Elsewhere in Don't Put It In Writing, here=E2=80=99s a Washington Post  boo=
k excerpt about Sean McElwee:
=E2=80=9CI literally have a daily calendar alert that says: =E2=80=98Don=E2=
=80=99t put s--- in texts,=E2=80=99 =E2=80=9D I once overheard Sean say at =
a party. His general advice for staff, he joked, was that =E2=80=9Cit=E2=80=
=99s not illegal if you do it over the phone.=E2=80=9D
This mantra, for him, appears to be about about=C2=A0avoiding embarrassment=
=C2=A0rather than=C2=A0doing crimes. But if you=C2=A0are=C2=A0doing crimes,=
 and you have a daily calendar alert=C2=A0saying =E2=80=9Cdon=E2=80=99t put=
 anything in texts,=E2=80=9D that=E2=80=99s definitely going to be part of =
the evidence against you at trial.

