In July 2022, I  talked to Sam Bankman-Fried at the Bloomberg Crypto Summit=
 about his process in bailing out various crypto shadow banks; the takeaway=
 was that Bankman-Fried was happy to lose some money on these bailouts in o=
rder to prop up confidence in the system. This was the correct analysis! It=
 was correct if Bankman-Fried was running one of the biggest and most lucra=
tive crypto exchanges and wanted crypto to be a good ecosystem for the long=
 term, and it was correct if he was running a big crypto scam and wanted hi=
s marks to be confident. The point is that a leveraged financial institutio=
n, good or bad, benefits from broad systemic confidence.


