<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A network of couriers who jointly smuggled mor=
e than =C2=A3100 million ($124 million) of criminal cash in suitcases from =
the UK to Dubai was found guilty following a trial of one of the largest mo=
ney laundering scams ever recorded.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In total 11 couriers have been convicted along=
side the ringleader, the National Crime Agency said Wednesday. In less than=
 a year, the couriers flew more than 80 flights, carrying cases full of dru=
g money. The group communicated on a Whatsapp group called=C2=A0<em>Sunshin=
e and Lollipops</em>.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I frequently <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/31291800.264436/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9=
vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTktMDEtMDQvZG9uLXQtY2FsbC1icmliZXMtY2hpY2tlbnM_Y2=
1waWQ9QkJEMDQyNjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld=
3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwNDI2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4=
b8524a319a23cBbfd7aa07" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targ=
et=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bo=
rder-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: =
solid; background-color: #ccc;"> point out</a> that giving bribes cutesy na=
mes in written communications is bad, because when you go to trial and a pr=
osecutor says =E2=80=9Cand in this email you promised a government official=
 =E2=80=981 million lollipops,=E2=80=99 and those weren=E2=80=99t lollipops=
 now were they,=E2=80=9D you will not have a good answer and will look very=
 guilty. Naming your money-laundering group chat =E2=80=9CSunshine and Loll=
ipops=E2=80=9D seems a little less obviously bad; you have to name the chat=
 something and everyone=E2=80=99s chats have dumb jokey names. Still the ju=
ry is not going to like you=C2=A0<em>more=C2=A0</em>for that name.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elsewhere in Don't Put It In Writing, here=E2=
=80=99s a Washington Post <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.co=
m/click/31291800.264436/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud2FzaGluZ3RvbnBvc3QuY29tL2xpZmVzdHl=
sZS8yMDIzLzA0LzI2L3NlYW4tbWNlbHdlZS13YXNoaW5ndG9uLWdhbWJsZXIv/607f07ceef4b8=
524a319a23cB4d1542b1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> book excerpt</a> about Sean McElwee:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI literally have a daily =
calendar alert that says: =E2=80=98Don=E2=80=99t put s--- in texts,=E2=80=
=99 =E2=80=9D I once overheard Sean say at a party. His general advice for =
staff, he joked, was that =E2=80=9Cit=E2=80=99s not illegal if you do it ov=
er the phone.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This mantra, for him, appears to be about abou=
t=C2=A0<em>avoiding embarrassment=C2=A0</em>rather than=C2=A0<em>doing crim=
es</em>. But if you=C2=A0<em>are=C2=A0</em>doing crimes, and you have a <em=
>daily calendar alert=C2=A0</em>saying =E2=80=9Cdon=E2=80=99t put anything =
in texts,=E2=80=9D that=E2=80=99s definitely going to be part of the eviden=
ce against you at trial.</p>
